http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/Leak-in-water-pipeline-leads-to-flooding-of-subway/article14015060.ece

The ‘flooding’ of the RBI subway on Rajaji Salai surprised motorists on Thursday. The flooding slowed down vehicle movement causing traffic congestion near Parry’s Corner.J. Balaji, who works for the RBI, said that the subway was inundated with over one foot of water and motorcyclists had a tough time due to this.Chennai Metrowater officials said the subway became flooded due the groundwater infiltration.The subway is close to the sea and located 25 feet beneath the ground. Chennai Corporation has laid a pipeline that collects the infiltrating seawater and groundwater. The pipeline is linked to two wells. This pipeline developed a breach on Thursday afternoon and this led to the water logging.Machines usedThe Metrowater deployed machines to drain out the water from the subway.Activists wanted to know the status of a proposal to renovate the subway.The Corporation had planned to renovate it at a cost of Rs. 97.75 lakh, but the proposal did take off, they said.Metrowater deployed machines to drain out the water from the subway